          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STANK"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  A large liquid scintillator tank, 50 cm in",
                " diameter and 50 cm in length, contained about 100",
                " litres of a Gd-loaded liquid (NE313)-neutron detection"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Fission chamber for fission fragment detection"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The nu-bar values averaged over the fast reactor",
                " neutron spectrum were calculated with the use of",
                " the program RELAT and the group constants of the",
                " different energy dependent variables were calculated",
                " with the program GRUSP in the multi-group structure",
                " chosen."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The observed nu values were integral values over the",
                " actual reactor neutron-energy spectrum.  The",
                " corrections to the observed integral values are,",
                " ------------------------------------------------------",
                "  correction  (per cent)           * Pu-239  * U-235",
                " ----------------------------------*---------*---------",
                "  spontaneous fission              * + 3.0   *  ---",
                "  pile-up correction               * - 0.1   * - 0.2",
                "  accidental coincidences          * + 0.2   * + 0.1",
                "  different fission neutron spectra* - 0.5   * - 0.8",
                "  bias level correction            * + 4.0   *  ---",
                "  fast neutron contribution in",
                "  thermal runs                     * - 0.8   * - 0.4",
                " ----------------------------------*---------*---------"
              ]
            }
          ],
